{"type":"message","id":"6435bde5","parentId":"479e9b66","timestamp":"2026-04-23T03:51:56.303Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"openclaw-weixin:1776916309644-34087e39\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-04-23 11:51 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\n# CLIProxyAPI basic server config\nhost: \"\"\nport: 8317\n# Credentials generated by OAuth logins are stored here.\nauth-dir: \"/root/.cli-proxy-api\"\n# Client auth keys used by your own tools when they call CLIProxyAPI.\n# This is not the upstream provider key.\napi-keys:\n - 48ch-wzC2qzxmQIBPq8mMXbQXRi454v8\nremote-management:\n# Enable Web UI and management API access from your LAN.\n allow-remote: true\n# Set a different value from api-keys above.\n secret-key: \"$2a$10$7WnG.OgYSfXfrgvKblhFg.lOv82Xk/cRllxO7tj08WlUpVacOQqGe\"\n disable-control-panel: false\nrequest-retry: 3\nquota-exceeded:\n switch-project: true\n switch-preview-model: true\n antigravity-credits: true\nlogging-to-file: true\nlogs-max-total-size-mb: 200\nws-auth: true\noauth-model-alias:\n codex:\n - name: gpt-5.4-mini\n alias: gpt-image-1024x1024\n fork: true\n - name: gpt-5.4-mini\n alias: gpt-image-1024x1536\n fork: true\n - name: gpt-5.4-mini\n alias: gpt-image-1536x1024\n fork: true\npayload:\n override-raw:\n - models:\n - name: gpt-image-1024x1024\n protocol: codex\n params:\n tool_choice: '{\"type\": \"image_generation\"}'\n tools: '[{\"type\":\"image_generation\", \"size\": \"1024x1024\", \"quality\": \"high\", \"background\": \"auto\"}]'\n - models:\n - name: gpt-image-1024x1536\n protocol: codex\n params:\n tool_choice: '{\"type\": \"image_generation\"}'\n tools: '[{\"type\":\"image_generation\", \"size\": \"1024x1536\", \"quality\": \"high\", \"background\": \"auto\"}]'\n - models:\n - name: gpt-image-1536x1024\n protocol: codex\n params:\n tool_choice: '{\"type\": \"image_generation\"}'\n tools: '[{\"type\":\"image_generation\", \"size\": \"1536x1024\", \"quality\": \"high\", \"background\": \"auto\"}]'\nopenai-compatibility:\n - name: openAi\n base-url: http://69.63.219.95:8080/v1\n api-key-entries:\n - api-key: [REDACTED] models:\n - name: gpt-5.4\n - name: gpt-5.4-mini\ndebug: true\n\n#\n# 1) Direct Codex-compatible API key\n# codex-api-key:\n# - api-key: \"sk-...\"\n#\n# 2) Gemini API key\n# gemini-api-key:\n# - api-key: \"AIza...\"\n#\n# 3) Claude-compatible API key\n# claude-api-key:\n# - api-key: \"sk-...\"\n#\n# 4) OpenAI-compatible relay, such as OpenRouter\n# openai-compatibility:\n# - name: \"openrouter\"\n# base-url: \"https://openrouter.ai/api/v1\"\n# api-key-entries:\n# - api-key: \"sk-or-v1-...\"\n# models:\n# - name: \"moonshotai/kimi-k2:free\"\n# alias: \"kimi-k2\""}],"timestamp":1776916316255}}
{"type":"message","id":"b45883b4","parentId":"6435bde5","timestamp":"2026-04-23T03:52:00.848Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_myHVPgWNB3KSwnYXvRhMA4SG|fc_0e1a3cd01f34f22f0169e9975ffcbc8197a234824bbd3c7608","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/skills/using-superpowers/SKILL.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"~/.openclaw/skills/using-superpowers/SKILL.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":80}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":50795,"output":39,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50834,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776916316303,"responseId":"resp_0e1a3cd01f34f22f0169e9975e72f881978b91f763348aab8e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"25ec5c1a","parentId":"b45883b4","timestamp":"2026-04-23T03:52:00.938Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_myHVPgWNB3KSwnYXvRhMA4SG|fc_0e1a3cd01f34f22f0169e9975ffcbc8197a234824bbd3c7608","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: using-superpowers\ndescription: Use when starting any conversation - establishes how to find and use skills, requiring Skill tool invocation before ANY response including clarifying questions\n---\n\n<SUBAGENT-STOP>\nIf you were dispatched as a subagent to execute a specific task, skip this skill.\n</SUBAGENT-STOP>\n\n<EXTREMELY-IMPORTANT>\nIf you think there is even a 1% chance a skill might apply to what you are doing, you ABSOLUTELY MUST invoke the skill.\n\nIF A SKILL APPLIES TO YOUR TASK, YOU DO NOT HAVE A CHOICE. YOU MUST USE IT.\n\nThis is not negotiable. This is not optional. You cannot rationalize your way out of this.\n</EXTREMELY-IMPORTANT>\n\n## Instruction Priority\n\nSuperpowers skills override default system prompt behavior, but **user instructions always take precedence**:\n\n1. **User's explicit instructions** (CLAUDE.md, GEMINI.md, AGENTS.md, direct requests) — highest priority\n2. **Superpowers skills** — override default system behavior where they conflict\n3. **Default system prompt** — lowest priority\n\nIf CLAUDE.md, GEMINI.md, or AGENTS.md says \"don't use TDD\" and a skill says \"always use TDD,\" follow the user's instructions. The user is in control.\n\n## How to Access Skills\n\n**In Claude Code:** Use the `Skill` tool. When you invoke a skill, its content is loaded and presented to you—follow it directly. Never use the Read tool on skill files.\n\n**In Gemini CLI:** Skills activate via the `activate_skill` tool. Gemini loads skill metadata at session start and activates the full content on demand.\n\n**In other environments:** Check your platform's documentation for how skills are loaded.\n\n## Platform Adaptation\n\nSkills use Claude Code tool names. Non-CC platforms: see `references/codex-tools.md` (Codex) for tool equivalents. Gemini CLI users get the tool mapping loaded automatically via GEMINI.md.\n\n# Using Skills\n\n## The Rule\n\n**Invoke relevant or requested skills BEFORE any response or action.** Even a 1% chance a skill might apply means that you should invoke the skill to check. If an invoked skill turns out to be wrong for the situation, you don't need to use it.\n\n```dot\ndigraph skill_flow {\n    \"User message received\" [shape=doublecircle];\n    \"About to EnterPlanMode?\" [shape=doublecircle];\n    \"Already brainstormed?\" [shape=diamond];\n    \"Invoke brainstorming skill\" [shape=box];\n    \"Might any skill apply?\" [shape=diamond];\n    \"Invoke Skill tool\" [shape=box];\n    \"Announce: 'Using [skill] to [purpose]'\" [shape=box];\n    \"Has checklist?\" [shape=diamond];\n    \"Create TodoWrite todo per item\" [shape=box];\n    \"Follow skill exactly\" [shape=box];\n    \"Respond (including clarifications)\" [shape=doublecircle];\n\n    \"About to EnterPlanMode?\" -> \"Already brainstormed?\";\n    \"Already brainstormed?\" -> \"Invoke brainstorming skill\" [label=\"no\"];\n    \"Already brainstormed?\" -> \"Might any skill apply?\" [label=\"yes\"];\n    \"Invoke brainstorming skill\" -> \"Might any skill apply?\";\n\n    \"User message received\" -> \"Might any skill apply?\";\n    \"Might any skill apply?\" -> \"Invoke Skill tool\" [label=\"yes, even 1%\"];\n    \"Might any skill apply?\" -> \"Respond (including clarifications)\" [label=\"definitely not\"];\n    \"Invoke Skill tool\" -> \"Announce: 'Using [skill] to [purpose]'\";\n    \"Announce: 'Using [skill] to [purpose]'\" -> \"Has checklist?\";\n    \"Has checklist?\" -> \"Create TodoWrite todo per item\" [label=\"yes\"];\n    \"Has checklist?\" -> \"Follow skill exactly\" [label=\"no\"];\n    \"Create TodoWrite todo per item\" -> \"Follow skill exactly\";\n}\n```\n\n## Red Flags\n\nThese thoughts mean STOP—you're rationalizing:\n\n| Thought | Reality |\n\n[36 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776916320899}}
{"type":"message","id":"c89a14b5","parentId":"25ec5c1a","timestamp":"2026-04-23T03:52:15.665Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"问题找到了，你这份 **YAML 缩进坏了**，所以 override 很可能根本没被正确解析。  \n最明显的是这段：\n\n```yaml\noauth-model-alias:\n codex:\n - name: gpt-5.4-mini\n alias: gpt-image-1024x1024\n fork: true\n```\n\n这里 `alias` 和 `fork` 没缩进到 `- name` 下面，同样 `payload.override-raw` 那几段也一样坏了。  \n结果就是看起来“有配置”，实际程序读进去的结构不对，所以 `tools` 没注入成功。\n\n你直接改成下面这个版本，基本就是文章里的正确结构：\n\n```yaml\noauth-model-alias:\n  codex:\n    - name: gpt-5.4-mini\n      alias: gpt-image-1024x1024\n      fork: true\n    - name: gpt-5.4-mini\n      alias: gpt-image-1024x1536\n      fork: true\n    - name: gpt-5.4-mini\n      alias: gpt-image-1536x1024\n      fork: true\n\npayload:\n  override-raw:\n    - models:\n        - name: gpt-image-1024x1024\n          protocol: codex\n      params:\n        tool_choice: '{\"type\":\"image_generation\"}'\n        tools: '[{\"type\":\"image_generation\",\"size\":\"1024x1024\",\"quality\":\"high\",\"background\":\"auto\"}]'\n\n    - models:\n        - name: gpt-image-1024x1536\n          protocol: codex\n      params:\n        tool_choice: '{\"type\":\"image_generation\"}'\n        tools: '[{\"type\":\"image_generation\",\"size\":\"1024x1536\",\"quality\":\"high\",\"background\":\"auto\"}]'\n\n    - models:\n        - name: gpt-image-1536x1024\n          protocol: codex\n      params:\n        tool_choice: '{\"type\":\"image_generation\"}'\n        tools: '[{\"type\":\"image_generation\",\"size\":\"1536x1024\",\"quality\":\"high\",\"background\":\"auto\"}]'\n```\n\n改完后记得：\n1. 保存配置\n2. 重启 CLIProxyAPI\n3. 再测一次\n\n如果你愿意，我下一条可以直接给你一份**完整可替换版配置文件**，把你现有内容一起整理好，避免手改再踩缩进坑。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e1a3cd01f34f22f0169e99765d0d081978627e08b5cc6efc0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":51724,"output":530,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52254,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776916320941,"responseId":"resp_0e1a3cd01f34f22f0169e9976255c881978241cb102af0ec41"}}
